How to use firestore migrator
install - build - run - import - export
https://github.com/codediodeio/firestore-migrator
----------------
Al Salam Alikom

download last version of firestore migrator script from this link:
https://github.com/codediodeio/firestore-migrator

extract project and open with vs code

go to this link:
https://console.firebase.google.com/project/<project_Id ex. test-76f4d>/settings/serviceaccounts/adminsdk

Press button: Generate new private key

save downloaded JSON file in your script root with name credentials.json

open terminal

npm install

npm update

npm run build

npm run build-link

now you are done !

----------------

to import files, simply push the target file in you script root folder

and run your migration code

----------------

to see all examples and options, please open this page:
https://github.com/codediodeio/firestore-migrator

